AccessConfig.data.192545-0: UDP allows devices to transmit data to the platform without establishing a connection. Provide lightweight and simple connections while allowing for a certain degree of packet loss.
AccessConfig.data.192545-1: TCP service is a connection oriented, reliable, byte stream based transport layer communication protocol. The device can establish a long-term connection with the platform through TCP services, update its status in real-time, and send messages.
